\c 12
\p
\v 1
\d To the director, according to the Sheminith, a psalm of David.
\q1
\v 2 Save, O YHWH, for the faithful are at an end,
\q1 For reliable people have vanished\f + NRSV.\f* from the sons of man.
\q1
\v 3 Each many speaks deceit to his neighbor,\f + Ps 15:2, 24:4.\f*
\q1 With flattering lips and a double heart they speak.
\q1
\v 4 May YHWH cut off all flattering lips,
\q1 The tongue that makes boasts.\f + Lit., "speaks great things."\f*
\q1
\v 5 Who say, "By our tongues we will be strong,
\q1 Our lips are with us, who is master over us?
\q1
\v 6 "Because of violence to the poor, because of the groans of the oppressed,
\q1 Now I will arise," says YHWH,
\q1 I will place (him) in the help for which he longs.\f + So ESV, NRSV. BDB: breathe, blow.\f*
\q1
\v 7 The words of YHWH are pure words,
\q1 Silver refined in the entrance to the land,\f + Check about text correction.\f*
\q1 Refined seven times.
\q1
\v 8 You O YHWH keep them,
\q1 You will guard us from this generation forever.
\q1
\v 9 The wicked walk around,
\q1 As vileness is exalted by the children of man.\f + Ps 15:4.\f*